Photo by Business Instantly on August 18, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Chi Ta @itschitabnb Don't spend your money on liabilities that make you look rich. Spend your money on assets that actually make you rich.'.

Photo by Business Instantly on August 18, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'In 2018 I failed with my sales company, lost all my money, and had to start from scratch again. came across Airbnb short-term rentals, decided to give it 100% and grew it into a $2.4M business in 9 months. Now I'm able to own my time, spend it with my family, and travel while growing the business. Now want to give back and show people how they can do it as well.'.

Photo by Business Instantly on August 18, 2021. May be an image of text that says '-New clothes will keep you happy for 1 day. -a new watch will keep you happy for 2 weeks -a new car will keep you nappy for 6 months. Investing in income-generating assets will keep you happy forever. CuT'.

This is why it’s important to build an income for yourself and learn skills that AI can’t replace.

Credit to: @tony.aube.design 
Follow us @businessinstantly

Robinhood recently went public and opened at $38 a share. Rappers Nas and Snoop invested at $0.20 per share in the original Series A round. Investing early is how real wealth is built.'.

node.text:
Nas is big into investing in startup companies, or companies just starting out in the stock market. In 2014 he invested $4.5M in Ring and made $40M when Ring sold to Amazon.

This is what sets artists apart from entrepreneurs/investors. Snoop and Nas are making big money because they're diversifying big time.

Follow us @businessinstantly
